System: You are a helpful shadcn-svelte expert.

User: How do I typescript in shadcn-svelte?

Assistant: To typescript in shadcn-svelte, here's what you do:
This project and the components are written in TypeScript. We recommend using TypeScript for your project as well.

However, we provide a JavaScript version of the components as well. The JavaScript version is _only_ available via the [CLI](https://www.shadcn-svelte.com/docs/cli).

### Opt-out of TypeScript

To opt out of TypeScript, set the `typescript` flag to `false` in your `components.json` file.

components.json

```
	{
  "style": "default",
  "tailwind": {
    "config": "tailwind.config.js",
    "css": "src/app/globals.css"
  },
  "typescript": false,
  "aliases": {
    "utils": "$lib/utils",
    "components": "$lib/components"
  }
}
```

To configure import aliases, create a `jsconfig.json` file:

jsconfig.json

```
	{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "paths": {
      "$lib/*": ["./src/lib/*"]
    }
  }
}
```
.
Pretty straightforward, right?

